background: An office supply company makes two types of printers: color printers and black and white printers.

parameters.definition: Maximum number of color printers that can be produced per day
Maximum number of black and white printers that can be produced per day
Maximum number of printers that the paper tray installing machine can equip per day
Profit generated per black and white printer

constraint.description: Number of color printers is an integer
constraint.code:
# Ensure the number of color printers produced is an integer
ColorPrinterProduced.vtype = grb.GRB.INTEGER

constraint.description: Number of black and white printers is an integer
constraint.code:
# Number of black and white printers is an integer
# No additional constraint needed as BWPrinterProduced is already defined as a binary variable

constraint.description: Number of color printers is non-negative
constraint.code: # This constraint does not require any code as it simply states that the number of color printers produced must be non-negative.

constraint.description: Number of black and white printers is non-negative
constraint.code:
# No code needed for this constraint as it simply enforces the non-negativity of the variable BWPrinterProduced in the binary context.
# The binary variable already inherently represents non-negativity, so no additional constraints are required.

constraint.description: The company can make at most MaxColor color printers per day
constraint.code:
# Add constraint for producing at most MaxColor color printers per day
model.addConstr(ColorPrinterProduced <= MaxColor, name="max_color_printer_production")

constraint.description: The company can make at most MaxBW black and white printers per day
constraint.code:
# Code for the constraint: "The company can make at most MaxBW black and white printers per day"
model.addConstr(BWPrinterProduced <= MaxBW, name="max_BW_printers_per_day")

constraint.description: The company can make at most a total of MaxTotal printers per day
constraint.code:
# Add constraint for the total number of printers produced per day
model.addConstr(TotalPrintersProduced <= MaxTotal, name="MaxTotal_printers_constraint")

constraint.description: Auxiliary constraint for integer requirement on number of color printers produced
constraint.code: # No code needed for this constraint as it specifies the possible values of a variable.

# Definition of TotalPrintersProduced constraint
model.addConstr(TotalPrintersProduced == ColorPrinterProduced + BWPrinterProduced, name="TotalPrintersProduced_constraint")

variables.definition: Binary variable indicating production of color printers
Binary variable indicating production of black and white printers
Total number of printers produced per day

objective.description: Maximize the company's profit, which is ProfitColor per color printer plus ProfitBW per black and white printer.
objective.code:
# Set objective
model.setObjective(ProfitColor * ColorPrinterProduced + ProfitBW * BWPrinterProduced, gp.GRB.MAXIMIZE)
